@vladima we only want to go to the ultimate location on named import and not all the time? Otherwise, I think this is not needed.

Do you expect to go to the ultimate location on this cases as well:

``` typescript
import a from './a';
let test = /*1*/a;
```

``` typescript
import a = require('./a');
let test = /*1*/a;
```

Maybe just add another rule that only on implicit alias(an alias you have to put the same name as the exported one), you go to the ultimate location?

So for instance:

``` typescript
import { a as b } from './a';
let c = b; // this will not go to ultimate.
```

``` typescript
import { a } from './a';
let c = a; // this will go to ultimate.
```

``` typescript
import a = require('./a');
let test = /*1*/a; // this will not go to ultimate.
```

Then we got more consistency.

